[{"id":"VR803589","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a portion of a large slab in the xz plane, centered at the origin. The slab extends from y equals negative d to y equals positive d in the y-direction and extends very far in the x- and z-directions.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR803589.g04.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A large slab is centered on the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x z\"><math alttext=\"x z\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi><mi>z</mi></math></span></span>-plane and extends very far in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>- and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"z\"><math alttext=\"z\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>z</mi></math></span></span>-directions. The slab extends from <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y equals negative d\"><math alttext=\"y equals negative d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mpadded><mo>-</mo><mi>d</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y equals positive d\"><math alttext=\"y equals positive d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y\"><math alttext=\"y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>y</mi></math></span></span>-direction, as shown. The slab has a current density directed in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive z\"><math alttext=\"positive z\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mi>z</mi></math></span></span>-direction given by <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector J equals a y squared times k hat\"><math alttext=\"vector J equals a y squared times k hat\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>J</mi><mo>â†’</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></span></span>.  The magnitude of the magnetic field at the top and bottom surfaces of the slab is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following is equal to the magnetic field at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y equals the fraction with numerator d, and denominator 2\"><math alttext=\"y equals the fraction with numerator d, and denominator 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR803589_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 B\"><math alttext=\"2 B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>B</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator B, and denominator 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator B, and denominator 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator B, and denominator 4\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator B, and denominator 4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>B</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator B, and denominator 8\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator B, and denominator 8\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>B</mi><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]